# {{PIPELINE_NAME}}

A [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code) skill that runs a {{N_FLOWS}}-step Pletor pipeline from a single natural-language command, generated by `pletor-pipeline-setup` on {{GENERATED_AT}}.

## What it does

{{PIPELINE_STEPS_BULLET_LIST}}

Before each step actually fires, the skill prints a preview table of exactly what's about to happen and waits for your Yes/No. **Nothing fires silently.**

Outputs land in a dated batch folder on your machine (under `<project_dir>/Outputs/`). If any of your flows has a Drive URL text input (set up at scaffold time), that flow also writes its outputs to a per-batch Drive folder — but Drive integration is optional and per-flow.

## How to use it

1. Drop input assets into `<project_dir>/Inputs/`
2. In Claude Code, type one of the trigger phrases:
   {{TRIGGER_PHRASES_BULLETS}}
3. Answer the questions Claude asks (run scope + batch label)
4. Review each step's preview table → answer Yes/No

That's it.

## How chaining works

For each step after the first, the skill auto-picks the **first successful output** of the previous step (alphabetical order of source filename). If you want a specific input to be promoted, prefix its filename with `01_`, `02_`, etc.

## Configuration

All behavior is driven by `config.json` in this skill directory. The most useful fields:

| Field | What it controls |
|---|---|
| `flows[].id` | Pletor flow UUID for each step |
| `flows[].label` | Short name shown in previews + folder names |
| `flows[].poll_timeout_seconds` | Per-run timeout for this step |
| `flows[].budget_warn` | Variation count that triggers a "you sure?" warning |
| `drive_root_id` | Google Drive folder ID where batch folders are created (leave empty if no flow uses Drive) |
| `rclone_remote` | Name of your rclone Drive remote (leave empty if no flow uses Drive) |
| `project_dir` | Local workspace (Inputs/ + Outputs/) |
| `env_file` | Path to your `.env` with `PLETOR_API_KEY` |

## File layout after first run

```
<project_dir>/
├── Inputs/                                   ← your assets
├── Outputs/
│   └── 2026-MM-DD_HHMMSS_<label>/
│       ├── <step_1_label>/    outputs from step 1
│       ├── <step_2_label>/    outputs from step 2  (if pipeline has 2+ steps)
│       ├── …
│       ├── manifest.json
│       └── README.md
└── asset_map.json                            ← cache: file → Pletor asset_id (so re-runs skip re-upload)
```

## Regenerating / editing this skill

If your Pletor flow definitions change (you add/remove inputs in the Pletor UI), delete `flows.json` from this skill directory — it'll be re-discovered on the next run.

To change the pipeline shape (add a step, swap a flow), edit `config.json` directly, or re-run `pletor-pipeline-setup` and overwrite this skill.

## Companion skill: `pletor-api`

For best results, install the **`pletor-api`** Claude Code skill alongside this one — it's the canonical reference for Pletor's REST API. Drop it at `~/.claude/skills/pletor-api/SKILL.md`. Get it from https://docs.pletor.ai/automate/api-integrations#agent-skills

It's used implicitly when:
- Debugging or extending `upload.py` (asset upload via REST)
- Writing any REST-direct alternative (bypassing the `prepare_batch` review flow)
- Handling Pletor error codes, retries, rate limits

This skill doesn't require it — but Claude is more reliable about REST details when both skills are loaded.

